## Summary

Three functions in `src/socket/SocketProxy.c` use inconsistent K&R brace style (opening brace on same line) instead of the project's GNU style (opening brace on new line).

## Style Issues

- [ ] `proxy_setup_tls_to_proxy` (lines 814-842) - K&R style braces
- [ ] `proxy_perform_sync_tls_handshake` (lines 844-893) - K&R style braces  
- [ ] `proxy_setup_after_tcp_connect` (lines 895-918) - K&R style braces

### Examples

**Current style (K&R):**
```c
if (conn->tls_ctx == NULL) {
    TRY {
      ...
    } EXCEPT (SocketTLS_Failed) {
```

**Project style (GNU):**
```c
if (conn->tls_ctx == NULL)
  {
    TRY
    {
      ...
    }
    EXCEPT (SocketTLS_Failed)
    {
```

The same file contains the correct style at lines 1260-1278 for the same code pattern.

## Scope

12 instances of same-line braces vs 75 instances of new-line braces in this file.

## Category

Refactoring - Code Style
